{"cursor":"25170","size":15,"audio":[],"cat":[],"tmpl":[],"currentlang":"en","linknr":792,"url":"Satellite_communications","article":"\n\n\nA 'communications satellite' or 'comsat' is an artificial satellite sent to\nspace for the purpose of telecommunications. Modern communications satellites\nuse a variety of orbits including geostationary orbits, Molniya orbits,\nelliptical orbits and low (polar and non-polar Earth orbits).\n\nFor fixed (point-to-point) services, communications satellites provide a\nmicrowave radio relay technology complementary to that of communication cables.\nThey are also used for mobile applications such as communications to ships,\nvehicles, planes and hand-held terminals, and for TV and radio broadcasting.\n","recorded":1362123957,"portal":[],"list":[],"links":"793","instances":["country_subdivision","telecommunication","biaxially_oriented","united_states","satellite","country","broadcasting","united_kingdom","satellite","telecommunications","telecommunications","japanese","satellite_communications","signal_processing","satellite","satellite","communications"],"pdf":["http://ntrs.nasa.gov/archive/nasa/casi.ntrs.nasa.gov/19660009169_1966009169.pdf","http://ntrs.nasa.gov/archive/nasa/casi.ntrs.nasa.gov/19660009169_1966009169.pdf","http://www.passeursdimages.fr/IMG/pdf/projections13.pdf","http://www.internationalcinematechnologyassociation.com/presentations/FRANCE-TELECOM-DIGITAL%20CINEMA-ShowEast-31st-October-2001-Bernard-PAUCHON-Managing-Director-Digital-Cinema-Program.pdf"],"categories":["American inventions","Communications satellites|","Satellite broadcasting"],"headings":["History","Structure","Applications","See also","References","External links"],"tags":[["point-to-point","telecommunications"],["pet_film","biaxially_oriented"],["general_post_office","united_kingdom"],["the_weather_channel","united_states"],["transponder","satellite_communications"],["iridium","satellite"],["molniya","satellite"],["transmission","telecommunications"],